  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your oven-proof dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1632224000920-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1632224000920-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1632224000920-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1632224000920-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin-10mm-Step-1-1632224000920-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Wash, then remove the <strong>leaves</strong> from your <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> and reserve them for later</p><p>Slice the <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> into 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>steak per person, approx. 3cm thick (use the middle part as it’s larger)</p><p>Tip: Save any leftover florets for another recipe!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632224049682-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632224049682-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632224049682-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632224049682-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632224049682-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cauliflower steak[s]</strong> to<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>a large <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges and add them to the dish[es]</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> roughly</p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven for an initial 30 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632224057668-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632224057668-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632224057668-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632224057668-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632224057668-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Mix the<strong> grated cheese</strong> with your<strong> cornflour </strong>in a jug</p><p>Add your<strong> single creamy soy</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until well combined – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632224085204-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632224085204-x400.jpg",
